    "title": "Kharoṣṭhī / Gāndhārī Lexicon",
    "description": "Kharosthi is an ancient abugida script used in Gandhara and Central Asia. Derived from Aramaic, it was deciphered by James Prinsep and others in the 1830s. Used extensively for Buddhist texts and Kushan-era inscriptions.",
